      "role": "assistant",
      "content": "For a truly sophisticated look, the baseline should always lean towards classic, tailored silhouettes, regardless of the specific event. Think dark, high-quality fabrics and impeccable fit—a well-cut suit or evening gown speaks louder than fleeting trends. Avoid anything overly flashy or loud; true class is understated and timeless. If you're aiming for universal high-class, stick to conservative elegance that doesn't draw unnecessary attention.",
