      "content": "okay, i get the \"conservative elegance\" thing. but what about when people want to incorporate their own cultural heritage into that? like, if someone is at a high-end international summit and wants to wear something more traditional, like a sari, a dashiki, or a kimono, would that still count as \"sophisticated\" and \"professional\" under these standards, or would it be seen as more of a \"cultural costume\" or something less formal than a suit?",
